<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-12-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-12-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/2802: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-12-15T13:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">December 15,
                                        1926—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 4:30
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>98. My No. 96, December 9, 8 p.m. Minister Gallardo informed me that he
                            communicated to the President, when the latter returned after <pb facs="0652" n="520" xml:id="pg_520"/> brief absence from the city,
                            the Brazilian Government’s reply which expresses the opinion that
                            intervention at Lima is inopportune at present moment for reasons that
                            have already been explained to Morgan. Although Argentina does not
                            contemplate any immediate action, Mr. Gallardo thinks that delay of
                            Government of Peru in replying to your memorandum is a favorable
                            sign.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>